The paper discusses routing protocols in VANET, which is a subclass of Mobile ad hoc networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the advantages/disadvantages and applications of these protocols, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the security aspects of these protocols, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the evolution of these protocols, which falls under the sub-category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper concludes with a comparison of the various routing protocols, which falls under the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
